From fcb47104fc2964e6f428ed7d4136b27b3ca999ac Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Harrison Ju <harrisonju@gmail.com>
Date: Sat, 7 Mar 2026 03:07:17 -0500
Subject: [PATCH 2/6] feat(zed): add PrisM as a native Zed language model
 provider
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Registers PrisM as a first-class LLM provider in the Zed editor fork.
PrisM speaks the OpenAI-compatible protocol, so the provider reuses
open_ai::stream_completion() and Zed's HttpClient — no reqwest conflict.

- Add PrismSettingsContent / PrismAvailableModel to settings_content
- Add PrismSettings to AllLanguageModelSettings with default api_url http://localhost:3000
- Implement PrismLanguageModelProvider + PrismLanguageModel in provider/prism.rs
- Support PRISM_API_KEY env var and in-editor API key configuration UI
- Register provider in register_language_model_providers()

Co-Authored-By: Claude Sonnet 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>
